Do you know that you will outlive the sun? do you know that when the earth and the stars have all passed away, you will just be beginning your endless day- a time without end? Once you are born, you will never cease to live, you will live forever. You will be alive eternally. ETERNITY HAS NO END!!!  This is a solemn and fearful truth. Suppose it were possible to tie a rope from the earth to the sun, and an ant were to go there (to the sun) and return on this rope; when the ant has done that a hundred times, only a small fraction of eternity would have passed. Suppose a small boy were to empty an ocean using a cup; the time it will take the boy to do so is a very tiny part of eternity. If it were possible to gather all the books that have ever been written in all fields of human Endeavour and in all languages, and a student were to read them all one by one; the time the student will spend reading all the books will only amount to a minute fraction of eternity. If a grain of sand represents on day, all the sand on the sea shore will represent only a small, neglible part of eternity! If a bird went to sharpen its beak once a year at a mountain, when the bird levels the mountain this way, only an insignificant part of eternity would have passed. 
ETERNITY! In short, is the life-time of the never-dying God. And you will be alive eternally. You will live for eternity, just as God is alive eternally. Once born, a person remains consciously alive forever. Eternity does not terminate at the time of date; death is just another wrung on the ladder of eternity. It is only a gateway to eternity- eternity in heaven or in hell. There is ‘THE RESURRECTION OF LIFE’ and there is the ‘resurrection of damnation’. This may surprise you. I pray it does. Every sinner will end up in eternal hell and every saint will go  up into eternal heaven. You will live forever in heaven or hell. There is no neutral place; there is nothing like purgatory. Jesus never mentioned anything or anywhere like that. You may say, ‘I am on the fence’. NO! There is no fence. You are either a born again, sanctified Christian, walking with the Holy Spirit or a sinner.
